solution.item: This is a DC calculation
At first we calculate the total resistance between the generator nodes
R12 and R11 connected in parallel so Rc=R12*R11/(R12+R11)=1.0000 Ohm
Rc and R10 connected in series so Rb=Rc+R10=2.0000 Ohm
R9 and R8 connected in parallel so Rh=R9*R8/(R9+R8)=1.0000 Ohm
Rh and R7 connected in series so Rg=Rh+R7=2.0000 Ohm
R4 and R5 connected in series so Rk=R4+R5=2.0000 Ohm
R2 and R1 connected in parallel so Rn=R2*R1/(R2+R1)=1.0000 Ohm
Rn and R3 connected in series so Rm=Rn+R3=2.0000 Ohm
Rk and Rm connected in parallel so Rj=Rk*Rm/(Rk+Rm)=1.0000 Ohm
Rg and Rj connected in series so Rf=Rg+Rj=3.0000 Ohm
Rf and R6 connected in series so Re=Rf+R6=4.0000 Ohm
Rb and Re connected in parallel so Ra=Rb*Re/(Rb+Re)=1.3333 Ohm
The total impedance is Ra = 1.3333 Ohm
Now we calculate the current on R1
We know that the voltage between VS1 nodes is 5.0000 V. So the current on VS1 is 5.0000/Ra = 3.7500 A
(1) The components Rb,Re connected in parallel. The voltage on Re is 5.0000 V because the voltage on Ra is 5.0000 V
(1) The current on Re is the 'voltage on Re / Re' = 1.2500 A .
(2) The components Rf,R6 connected in series.
(2) The voltage between this components starting and ending node is 5.0000 V.
(2) Rf is in the voltage divider so the voltage on Rf is Rf/Re*5.0000 V = 3.7500 V.
(2) The current on Rf is the 'voltage on Rf / Rf' = 1.2500 A .
(3) The components Rg,Rj connected in series.
(3) The voltage between this components starting and ending node is 3.7500 V.
(3) Rj is in the voltage divider so the voltage on Rj is Rj/Rf*3.7500 V = 1.2500 V.
(3) The current on Rj is the 'voltage on Rj / Rj' = 1.2500 A .
(4) The components Rk,Rm connected in parallel. The voltage on Rm is 1.2500 V because the voltage on Rj is 1.2500 V
(4) The current on Rm is the 'voltage on Rm / Rm' = 0.6250 A .
(5) The components Rn,R3 connected in series.
(5) The voltage between this components starting and ending node is 1.2500 V.
(5) Rn is in the voltage divider so the voltage on Rn is Rn/Rm*1.2500 V = 0.6250 V.
(5) The current on Rn is the 'voltage on Rn / Rn' = 0.6250 A .
(6) The components R2,R1 connected in parallel. The voltage on R1 is 0.6250 V because the voltage on Rn is 0.6250 V
(6) The current on R1 is the 'voltage on R1 / Ro' = 0.3125 A .
